In his speech at the Hotel Washington, President Joe Biden thanked his supporters and highlighted the achievements of his administration in the past year. He mentioned the passage of the American Rescue Plan, the drop in unemployment rate, and the success of the COVID-19 vaccination campaign. He also emphasized the importance of the Build Back Better plan and the need to address issues such as childcare, healthcare costs, climate change, and voting rights. President Biden expressed optimism about America's future and urged unity among Democrats for the upcoming 2022 elections.